article.headline: IPFW 100, S. Dakota St. 66
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- David Carson had 24 points and 10 rebounds to lead five IPFW players in double figures as the Mastodons beat South Dakota State 100-66 Friday night in the Summit League. Deilvez Yearby had 18 points and nine rebounds for IPFW (6-9, 1-3). Jakari Johnson scored 17, John Peckinpaugh 11 and Ben Botts 10 for the Mastodons, who outrebounded the Jackrabbits 42-29. IPFW opened on a 10-0 run and never trailed, taking a 55-18 halftime lead. The Mastodons, who shot 38-of-71 from the field including 9-of-16 from three-point range, led by as many as 46 points during the second half. South Dakota State (6-10, 1-3) never got closer than 32 after the break. Garett Callahan led the Jackrabbits with 12 points. Kal Williams added 10.
